      <div id="right_content">
        <div class="content_title">FAQs In Chinese Language Study </div>
        <div class="content_text">
          <div class="layout_2">
            <div class="show-hide">
  <ul class="blue_arrow">
    <li class="title"><a href="#">About Chinese language study</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> You are expected to earnestly participate in the studying and testing of all subjects required by the curriculum. </li>

<li> New students will be required to sit for a  placement test. They will be placed into classes based on their  performance in the placement test. </li>

<li> Before the new semester starts, the school will  announce the information regarding the division of students into classes  and school timetable at the bulletin boards in the lecture building,  the student dorm, as well as in the office of the school. Such  information will also be released at http://www.sie.sjtu.edu.cn. </li>

<li> In the first week of the new semester, you may  attend the class you are placed in on a trial basis. If you find this  class does not fit with your Chinese level, you may go to the Office of  Educational Affairs to request a transfer to another class during the  second week. The school will address such requests according to specific  circumstances. You cannot change classes by yourself. </li>

<li> If you ask for leave for one day or less, you  only need to get approval from your class teacher who will report to the  Office of Educational Affairs for record. But if the leave of absence  exceeds one day, you must get approval from the Office yourself. If the  leave of absence exceeds three days, the Office must report to the Dean  for approval. If you do not attend school without asking for leave or  you fail to get an approval, it will be dealt with as an absence without  leave.</li>

</ul>
</div>
    </li>
<li class="title"><a href="#">About textbooks</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> You should buy the textbooks according to the level of class you are assigned to at the registration of each semester. </li>

<li> If you need to transfer to another class one  week after the semester begins, you may go to the designated place (to  be announced by the school at registration) to buy new textbooks. You  may return the old textbooks if they are not written on or spoilt.</li>

<li> You cannot return textbooks for elective courses.</li>
</ul>

</div>
   </li>
<li class="title"><a href="#">Assessment and score report</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> Assessments are made on a semester basis, which consists of classroom performance, mid-term exams and final exams. </li>

<li> Classroom performance includes your class attendance, attentiveness and the quality of your homework. Full marks are 100. </li>

<li> Mid-term exams are held during the 10 th week of  every semester, with final exams during the 20 th week. Full marks for  both exams are 100. </li>

<li> The overall grades for each course in each  semester are made up of three parts, namely classroom performance (10%),  mid-term exam (20%) and final exam (70%). </li>

<li> In the case that the total amount of your  absence (an accumulation of sick leave, business leave and absence  without leave) in terms of class hours exceeds one third of the time  required by a given course, you are not allowed to take the final exam  of that course. </li>

<li> Failure in two or more courses in terms of the  overall grades of every semester will disqualify you from moving up to a  higher level of study in the next semester.</li>
</ul>

</div>
    </li>
<li class="title"><a href="#">The issuance of the certificate for the Chinese language learners</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<p>If you have finished and passed all the courses, you will get a Certificate of Completion.</p>
<p>The minimum standards to get a certificate:</p>
<ul class="blue_arrow"><li>Your attendance must account for 2/3 or more of the total class periods.</li>
<li>You should finish the work assigned by the teacher. You must attend the quizzes, the mid-term exam, final exam, and so on.</li>
<li>You should pay all the fees and make all the necessary procedures before the courses finish.</li>
<li>There is no severe violation of the laws and regulations.</li>
</ul>
</div>
    </li>
<li class="title"><a href="#">Dropping out halfway</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> If you are unable to continue your planned study  for various reasons, you must apply to the Office of Educational  Affairs one week in advance and fill out the "Application Form for  Quitting School ". </li>

<li> If you hold a student visa (X type), you should go to the Office of Enrollment to change the expiry date of your visa. </li>

<li> Please refer to the relevant provisions as set  out in Payment and Refund of Tuition Fee for the calculation of the  refund of tuition fee. </li>

<li> If you stay at the student dorm offered by the  school, you should go to the Office of Students Affairs who will help  you to check out of the dorm. Accommodation fee will be charged  according to the "Contract of Lodging". Staff from the dorm management  will check to see if there is any damage to the room furnishings and  articles lent for dorm use. Any damage and loss incurred will be  compensated for using the occupant's room deposit. </li>
</ul>
</div>
    </li>

<li class="title"><a href="#">Elective courses</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> The school offers several elective courses every  semester. When the new semester starts, the school will announce the  information regarding the elective courses, the division of students  into classes and the school timetable at the bulletin boards in the  lecture building, the student dorm, as well as in the office of the  school. Such information will also be released online: <a title="Ziinkified: http://www.sie.sjtu.edu.cn" href="http://www.sie.sjtu.edu.cn/">http://www.sie.sjtu.edu.cn</a> . Elective courses begin in the 4 th week of each semester. </li>

<li> You can choose the elective courses of your own  interest as long as their class times are not conflicting with the  regular courses. But the number of elective courses to be taken is  limited to 2 for every semester. </li>

<li> You should submit your application for elective  courses to the Office of Educational Affairs in the 3 rd week of every  semester for approval. </li>

<li> The number of places is limited for each  elective course and no further application will be accepted when there  are no more vacancies. </li>

<li> Tuition is waived for all the elective courses,  but you need to pay an enrollment fee, fees for textbooks and teaching  materials. The fee for teaching materials of each course is listed in  the notice for elective courses issued every semester. If you want to  quit the elective courses halfway, you will get no refund of the paid  fees. </li>

<li> There are no set exams for elective courses, hence no score report or certificate of study will be issued. </li>
</ul>
</div>
    </li>
<li class="title"><a href="#">Reward and punishment</a>
    <div class="content_text_4">
<ul class="blue_arrow">
<li> Students who observe the rules and regulations  of the school, abide by the Chinese laws and decrees, study hard, show  proper respect to their teachers, get along well with their fellow  students and achieve excellent results in their study may apply for the  scholarship offered by the school every year. The school will announce  the specific date of application and criteria for appraisal in due time. </li>

<li> Students who violate the rules and regulations of  the school will receive penalties ranging from disciplinary warning or  order to quit school according to the nature of the violation. </li>
</ul>
</div>
    </li>

</ul>
</div>
          </div>
        </div>
